<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFFFFC0FF71FF68FC7EFE26" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FF68FB27FF56" blockId="23.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFFFFC0FF79FF68FF05FF7A" box="[159,248,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="69.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[211,1383,199,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-19@69.[195,1393,181,1905]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURE 16. Eudocima phalonia group and Hemiceratoides adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605543/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs 16</figureCitation>
: A–B, 21: J, 28: C–L, 32: M, 33: E–F, M–N, 34: G–H, 35: G–H, 36: G, 37: C–D, H–I, 38: H–I, 40: A–B, 41: F, 42: A, D, 45: B–C, G 46: H, 47: H–I, 49: C, F, 53: C, F, 55: C, F, 57: B, 58: C, G, 92: A, G)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FED0FC7EFE26" blockId="23.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
A diagnosis of this 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFFFFC0FE88FED0FE08FEB2" box="[366,501,258,284]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
endemic species is covered in the 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FC90FED1FC0EFEB2" authorityName="Borth &amp; Kons" authorityYear="2021" box="[886,1011,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afrikana">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FC90FED1FC0EFEB2" box="[886,1011,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. afrikana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
description. Other 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFFFFC0FB2CFED0FAACFEB2" box="[1226,1361,258,284]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FABEFED0FF30FEEE" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FABEFED0FF30FEEE" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FEC9FEF5FE42FEEE" baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[303,447,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperator">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FEC9FEF5FE42FEEE" box="[303,447,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. imperator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FE10FEF5FD97FEEE" box="[502,618,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FE10FEF5FD9BFEEE" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[502,614,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">E. boseae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but in each of those species the hindwing medial patch is fused with the marginal band. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FEA1FE98FDF3FECA" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[327,526,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FEA1FE98FDF3FECA" box="[327,526,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima boseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much smaller and lacks the orange dorsal abdomen. It could also be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FF36FEBDFEB3FE26" baseAuthorityName="Brou &amp; Zilli" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[208,334,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lequeuxi">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FF36FEBDFEB3FE26" box="[208,334,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. lequeuxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but that species is only found on mainland Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
